<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="388" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,699,786,811]" box="[151,699,786,811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,786,811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<typeStatus box="[151,204,787,811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Hampson, 1898" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Singh &amp; Ranjan" authorityYear="2019" box="[298,699,787,811]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[298,532,787,811]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Botyodes crocopteralis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson, G. F." box="[538,699,787,811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="590 - 761" refId="ref2847" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) A revision of the moths of the subfamily Pyraustinae and family Pyralidae Part 1. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London, 1898 (4), 590 - 761, pls. 49 - 50. [pp. 710]" type="journal article" year="1898">Hampson, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,857,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
The new genus is described here as monotypic for its 
<typeStatus box="[740,788,858,884]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Singh &amp; Ranjan" authorityYear="2019" box="[888,1066,857,883]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[888,1066,857,883]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">B. crocopteralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Originally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hampson, 1898" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[1204,1352,857,883]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">crocopteralis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson, G. F." pageId="1" pageNumber="388" pagination="590 - 761" refId="ref2847" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) A revision of the moths of the subfamily Pyraustinae and family Pyralidae Part 1. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London, 1898 (4), 590 - 761, pls. 49 - 50. [pp. 710]" type="journal article" year="1898">Hampson, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[570,673,893,919]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[570,673,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Botyodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a female representative from 
<collectingRegion box="[1173,1258,893,919]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson, G. S. &amp; Tuck, K. R. &amp; Shaffer, M." pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref3559" refString="Robinson, G. S., Tuck, K. R. &amp; Shaffer, M. (1994) A field guide to the smaller moths of South-East Asia. Malaysian Nature Society, Kuala Lumpur, 309 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Robinson 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al.</emphasis>
(1994)
</bibRefCitation>
commented on the sexual dimorphism of this species and provided images of both male and female adults.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,857,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,471,965,992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Diagnostic characters:</emphasis>
Strong sexual dimorphism. In males, forewings fuscous black with an oblique and broad orange band from middle of costa to anal angle, slightly constricted at middle. In females, forewings orange yellow with markings fuscous brown, ante-medial spot on median nervure, a reniform on disco-cellular, a postmedial spot below vein Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[453,461,1091,1105]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">2</subScript>
, whole apical area black with rounded inner edge. A complex pattern of dark grey and white is present on the underside of thorax and on the legs. This pattern is identical in both the sexes (
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson, G. S. &amp; Tuck, K. R. &amp; Shaffer, M." pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref3559" refString="Robinson, G. S., Tuck, K. R. &amp; Shaffer, M. (1994) A field guide to the smaller moths of South-East Asia. Malaysian Nature Society, Kuala Lumpur, 309 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Robinson 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al.</emphasis>
1994
</bibRefCitation>
). Male genitalia with a broad, inverted “U” shaped uncus having a minute notch at apex; unornamented, tongue shaped valvae with a prominent thumb like process from inner wall of basal half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="388" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,857,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1217,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The forewing marking of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" box="[638,822,1217,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[638,822,1217,1243]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">N. crocopteralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[841,954,1217,1244]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,176,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1427,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1, Botyodes asialis, ♂, NE India, Mizoram, 2, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram; 3, Botyodes principalis, ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 4, ditto, ♀, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh; 5, Neobotyodes crocopteralis, gen. &amp; comb. nov., ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 6, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255391/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Figs. 5, 6</figureCitation>
) are very distinct and unmistakable from the members of its parental genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[549,652,1253,1279]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[549,652,1253,1279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Botyodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where the sexual dimorphism is absent and generally, the moths of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[151,254,1289,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,254,1289,1315]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Botyodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are with yellowish ground colour having brownish bands at post-medial region of forewing. Antennae of males are simple in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" box="[371,551,1325,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[371,551,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">N. crocopteralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[682,785,1325,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[682,785,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Botyodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, antennae of male bear four teeth on the basal joint enclosing a hollow. In male genitalia: a small, inverted ‘U’ shaped uncus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" box="[1020,1168,1361,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[1020,1168,1361,1387]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">crocopteralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1185,1268,1361,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1764]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,187,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1719]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Male genitalia. 19, 20, Neobotyodes crocopteralis, gen. &amp; comb. nov. 21–23, Caldubotys caldusalis gen. &amp; comb. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255397/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) is completely different from a long, curved uncus having setosed and spatulated head with a quadra-radiated base in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[1330,1436,1397,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asialis">
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">B. asialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[159,209,1433,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">type</typeStatus>
of genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[321,424,1433,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,424,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Botyodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[449,585,1433,1459]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1985,2010]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,457,1956]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,446,1964]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Male genitalia. 11–14, Botyodes asialis; 15–18, Botyodes principalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255395/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Figs. 11–14</figureCitation>
). Simple tegumen and narrow, elongated valvae with a strong process from inner wall of basal half in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" box="[442,590,1469,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[442,590,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">crocopteralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is entirely distinct from a tegumen having quadra-radiated tip (modified for attachment of uncus having similar base), and a complex valvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[905,1009,1505,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asialis">
<emphasis box="[905,1009,1505,1531]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">B. asialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1308,1541,1568]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,857,1676]" box="[199,1308,1541,1568]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1542,1568]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Etymology:</emphasis>
New generic name refers to the relationship of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hampson" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" box="[872,1134,1541,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[872,1020,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">crocopteralis</emphasis>
Hampson
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[1198,1301,1541,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1198,1301,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Botyodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
